# Documentation rules

- `/docs` is the **canonical source of truth** for career + portfolio content
  and engineering governance. Update it **before** `/src`.
- Mapping of docs → components is in `docs/README.md` and
  `.claude/WORKFLOWS.md`. Follow the update contracts exactly.
- When content/behavior changes, update the matching `docs/` file and, if
  quality changed, `docs/governance/*` (checklist, technical-debt, backlog,
  roadmap, audit-report).
- Record significant decisions as ADRs (`docs/architecture/architecture-decisions.md`
  and `.ai/decisions`).
- Keep `.ai/memory/*`, `mcp.json`, and `llms.txt` current so AI clients stay
  oriented.
- Prose: clear, concise, absolute dates. Don't duplicate content across files —
  link to the canonical one.
